<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n10137e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10137e">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10137e"> 137(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> peacock sees with / eye of its tail</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Argus, fils d&apos;Arestor, avait cent yeux, dont cinquante restaient ouverts pendant que le sommeil fermait les cinquante autres. Junon lui confia la garde d&apos;Io chang&eacute;e en vache ; mais Mercure endormit au son de sa fl&ucirc;te ce gardien vigilant, et lui coupa la t&ecirc;te. Junon, d&eacute;sol&eacute;e et d&eacute;&ccedil;ue, <mark>prit les yeux d&apos;Argus et les r&eacute;pandit sur la queue du paon</mark>. <font color="green">[Argus, son of Arestor, had a hundred eyes, fifty of which remained open while sleep closed the remaining fifty. Juno confided to him the keeping of Io, transformed into a cow; but Mercury put this watchful guardian to sleep with the sound of his flute and cut off his head. Juno, aggrieved and deluded, took the eyes of Argus and spread them upon the tail of the peacock.]</font> <small> P. Commelin, <a name="NMGR" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#NMGR"><cite title="source">Nouvelle Mythologie</cite></a> (1907) 60</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
